entry.title: Use common ancestor clip when layer escapes clip of render surface
entry.content:
A layer contributing to a render surface may have a clip state that

is not a descendant of the clip state of the render surface's effect.

This happens at least when a -web-box-reflect element has a

descendant that is not contained by the former. Previously we didn't

apply clip to the render surface, causing the reflection to overflow

ancestor clips, sometimes including the clip of an iframe.



We could change blink to avoid the situation (which would change web

API), but I think we should harden the logic when such situation

occurs. Now behind a kill switch RenderSurfaceCommonAncestorClip,

instead of ignoring all clips, we let the render surface clip to the

common ancestor clip of the clip of the render surface's effect and

the clips of all contributing layers. This can at least prevent

filtered contents from overflowing frames.

The GestureConsumer effectively owns the GestureProvider through a

map from the consumer to a unique pointer of the provider, however

destroyed consumer.

entry.title: Never break before a float resumed after a break.
entry.content:
Always process all incoming inline break tokens that establish a

parallel flow for a fragmented float or overflowed block-in-inline.



The orphans implementation works so that if we run out of space in a

fragmentainer, we'll still keep on laying out a few more lines, to

figure out if we should break further up (rather than exactly where we

run out of space), in order to honor widows. We count the number of

lines laid out. The fix is to make sure that inline break tokens that

just contain a resumed float or block-in-inline (in a parallel flow)

leave this counter alone. Otherwise we risk breaking before even getting

around to resuming the block node inside, which means that it wouldn't

be added to the fragment tree at all.



Add DCHECKs after layout of a block to make sure that we don't break at

a location where we'll be unable to resume correctly. This also includes

DCHECKing block break tokens, not just inline break tokens. There are no

known issues for block layout ending up in this state, but it would be

equally bad if it happens.



This also fixes a correctness issue that was introduced by CL:4874801.

Counting resumed floats as line boxes for orphans / widows consideration

caused us to break prematurely in some cases. If this premature break is

before an actual line box, we get a correctness issue (breaking too

soon). If this premature break is before a resumed float, the fragment

tree would be in a bad state, which could lead to crashes.



Add a test for both a crash and the correctness issue.

entry.title: Make getting displayed notifications work with notification attribution.
entry.content:
Getting all currently displayed notifications would be impractical to

implement when notifications can be spread across arbitrary many

applications/processes (we don't want to launch every app shim that

could possibly be showing notifications on Chrome startup). Fortunately

little is lost by not implementing this, and instead implementing a

narrower "get displayed notifications for a specific origin" method.



So this CL introduces the latter method, uses it instead of the former

method when getting notifications to return to a website when it

requests displayed notifications. The main effect of this is that Chrome

on Mac (when notification attribution is enabled) will no longer clean

up no longer displayed notifications from its database on startup;

rather these will be cleaned up when either a site queries this

information, or when they expire.

entry.title: [Android DevX] Lldb: Enable alternative NDK selection.
entry.content:
It was found that lldb.sh from Android NDK r25c does not attach to

lldb-server running on an emulator on cloudtops. However, the problem

goes away in r26.



Instead of the more arduous fixes of rolling the NDK or finding the

root cause of the bug, this CL implements a workaround: Allow Android

wrapper scripts to specify alternative NDK (e.g., r26) than the default

(currently r25c). So now one can run:

$OUTDIR/chrome_public_apk lldb --ndk-dir=$ABSOLUTE_NDK_DIR



Also, improve the script to exit gracefully when the above bug

manifests, by properly killing lldb-server on device. Details:



* apk_operations.py:

* Add switches {--ndk-dir, --lldb-server, --lldb}, and forward them to

connect_lldb.sh.

* connect_lldb.sh:

* Store PID of on-device lldb-server and kill it on exit. This is

needed since the current method (kill the local sh script that

launches on-device lldb-server) does not kill lldb-server.

* Fix NDK_DIR check: "-f" should be "-d".

* get_ndk_lldb_server():

* Check both lib64/ and lib/ to accommodate different NDK versions.

* Stop depending on parsing 3pp/install.sh to get CLANG_VERSION for

toolchains/llvm/.../clang/$CLANG_VERSION

subdir: Just assume it's the only subdir, then use readpath and

wildcard.

entry.title: view-transition: Fix flaky view-transition tests
entry.content:
In particular, this should fix root-and-nested-element-transition.html

but the pattern is seen across other tests in this directory.



Most view-transition-on-navigation reftests navigate themselves to a

destination page and take a screenshot of the view transition.



However, the destination is missing "reftest-wait" on the

documentElement. This is not equivalent to removing "reftest-wait" on

the outgoing page. Removing "reftest-wait" will double-raf[1] in order

to ensure the CopyOutputRequest captures the current state from Blink.

However, navigating to a new page without "reftest-wait" will notifyDone

~immediately[2] which may capture the still-visible old page (especially

as rendering may be blocked in the new page due to view transition

capture requests).



This CL updates all these tests to ensure destination pages have

"reftest-wait" to ensure they double-raf before taking the pixel dump.

Waiting on rAF should be enough since the first rAF must come after the

view transition capture is finished and pseudos are visible.



[1] https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:content/web_test/renderer/test_runner.cc;l=498;drc=a6bdc8f2993883fc55eb9cb0945694299b056675

[2] https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:content/web_test/renderer/test_runner.cc;l=512;drc=a6bdc8f2993883fc55eb9cb0945694299b056675

entry.title: Added metrics for kAutofillUseAddressRewriterInProfileSubsetComparison
entry.content:
This CL:

-Adds a metric `Autofill_AcceptedPreviouslyHiddenSuggestion` that logs

when the user accepts a suggestion that would have been hidden without

the feature.

-Adds a metric `Autofill.ProfilesDifferOnAddressLineOnly` that logs

whether two profiles A and B, with A.IsSubsetOfForFieldSet(B) evaluating

to true without the feature, starts evaluating to false with the feature

enabled.

-Adds tests for the added metrics.
